# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Joy — AI Recruiter | Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OpenAI — Required for resume scoring, email, JD generation, TTS, voice routing
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Twilio — Required for calling + SMS features
# Get from: https://console.twilio.com
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+1XXXXXXXXXX

# Gmail SMTP — Set in the sidebar at runtime, no .env needed
# But you can hardcode here if deploying for a single user:
# GMAIL_ADDRESS=you@gmail.com
# GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SETUP NOTES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. OpenAI:
#    - Go to platform.openai.com → API keys → create one
#    - Models used: gpt-4o-mini (text), tts-1 (voice)
#
# 2. Twilio:
#    - Free trial: call verified numbers only
#    - Upgrade ($) to call any Indian number
#    - Voice uses Amazon Polly Aditi (en-IN) via TwiML
#
# 3. Gmail App Password:
#    - myaccount.google.com → Security → 2-Step Verification
#    - Then: App Passwords → Mail → Generate
#    - Use the 16-char password, NOT your Gmail password
#
# 4. Voice recognition:
#    - Uses browser Web Speech API (no API key needed)
#    - Works in Chrome and Edge only
#    - Wake words: "Hey Joy", "OK Joy", "Hi Joy", "Joy"
#
# 5. To run locally:
#    pip install -r requirements.txt
#    export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...    (or use python-dotenv)
#    streamlit run playground.py
